Update existing themes to use Bootstrap 4
Remove Amelia and Readable themes, since they aren't available in Bootswatch 4

Port mkdocs/mkdocs#1935 to the bootswatch themes

This patch uses `scroll-padding-top` to indicate that when the user clicks on
an anchor and the browser scrolls to it, the anchor should have that amount of
padding on the top, thus neatly accommodating the fixed nav header without any
gross hacks!

Fix padding/background color issues with hljs code blocks after #50

Prior to using hljs_style, mkdocs-bootswatch used lightly-modified versions of
the themes, removing the padding and background color from the .hljs
selectors. This patch restores the previous behavior by overriding those
rules.
Bump version to 1.0.
Add release notes to README.md

commit.message:
Update dependencies

- PY33
+ PY36
+ PY37
+ PYPY
+ PYPY3
+ MkDocs>=1.0
HTTPS link to demo page

Use hljs_style config option.

Made possable by mkdocs/mkdocs#1556.

Also fixes highlighting. Previously it was ignoring the hosted style as 
the CDN was being used. Now the CDN points to the correct style for each 
theme.

Inherit from mkdocs

This should drasticaly reduce the maintance burden of these themes. 
Except for CSS, everything is now inherited from the `mkdocs` theme 
which ships with MkDocs. Fixes #39.
Please include license text in pypi release.

Update IE8 Polyfills to latest versions

https://getbootstrap.com/docs/3.3/getting-started/#template
